0who%20had%20suddenly%20died%20from%20a%20heart%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmerson's%20lawyers%20said%20he%20had%20an%20unusual%20reaction%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fafter-alaska-airlines-incident-union-warns-about-magic-mushrooms-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epsilocybin%2C%20the%20active%20ingredient%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20drug.%20He%20was%20left%20feeling%20detached%20from%20reality%20for%20several%20days%2C%20a%20condition%20known%20as%20Hallucinogen%20Persisting%20Perception%20Disorder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmerson%20%26quot%3Bbelieved%20he%20was%20either%20trapped%20in%20a%20dream%20or%20already%20dead%2C%26quot%3B%20his%20lawyers%20wrote%20in%20a%20sentencing%20memo%20filed%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20add%20that%20he%20didn't%20believe%20Flight%202059%20was%20real%2C%20but%20he%20boarded%20because%20he%20believed%20it%20would%20help%20him%20wake%20up%20and%20see%20his%20family%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20the%20flight%20home%2C%20he%20became%20increasingly%20suspicious%20that%20the%20airplane%20would%20never%20make%20it%20home%2C%20and%20that%20he%20would%20endlessly%20fly%2C%20never%20reaching%20his%20destination%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20document%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20trying%20to%20shut%20down%20the%20engines%2C%20the%20pilots%20intervened%2C%20and%20Emerson%20left%20the%20cockpit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20he%20became%20convinced%20he%20was%20in%20a%20dream%20because%20he%20was%20surprised%20by%20how%20calm%20the%20passengers%20seemed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmerson%20then%20put%20his%20hand%20in%20a%20pot%20of%20hot%20coffee%20to%20try%20to%20wake%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20he%20told%20the%20flight%20attendants%20he%20couldn't%20distinguish%20what%20was%20real%20and%20asked%20them%20to%20cuff%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20flight%20diverted%2C%20Emerson%20was%20arrested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20jail%2C%20he%20began%20journaling%2C%20where%20he%20realized%20he%20had%20been%20an%20alcoholic%20for%20years%2C%20his%20lawyers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpilot-mental-illness-faa-regulations-joseph-emerson-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eavoided%20mental%20health%20treatment%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20he%20was%20struggling%20to%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20his%20friend's%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmerson%20has%20since%20started%20a%20nonprofit%20with%20his%20wife%20called%20Clear%20Skies%20Ahead%2C%20aimed%20at%20creating%20awareness%20of%20this%20problem%20within%20aviation.%20Many%20pilots%20may%20try%20to%20avoid%20treatment%20for%20mental%20health%2C%20as%20doing%20so%20can%20lead%20to%20them%20losing%20their%20license%20to%20fly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmerson%20initially%20faced%20up%20to%2020%20years%20in%20prison.%20He%20pleaded%20guilty%20in%20September%2C%20and%20the%20government%20has%20requested%20a%2012-month%20prison%20sentence.%20A%20pre-sentence%20report%20also%20suggested%20six%20months%20of%20home%20detention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmerson%20is%20asking%20for%20credit%20for%20time%20served%20and%20probation%20instead.%20He%20is%20set%20to%20appear%20in%20an%20Oregon%20court%20for%20sentencing%20next%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falaska-airlines-pilot-magic-mushrooms-engine-shutdown-trapped-in-dream-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1763120207000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69170e51abd5e944effabb2d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falaska-airlines-pilot-magic-mushrooms-engine-shutdown-trapped-in-dream-2025-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Joseph%20Emerson%20attempted%20to%20shut%20down%20a%20plane's%20engines%20mid-flight%20after%20magic%20mushrooms%20left%20him%20feeling%20detached%20from%20reality%20for%20several%20days.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22psyme%40businessinsider.com