img%20width%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mark%20Zuckerberg%20poses%20for%20photographers%20in%20New%20York%2C%20October%202025%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69165c5be1a9cbb014de30c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222432%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMark%20Zuckerberg's%20Meta%20launched%20Reels%20as%20a%20TikTok%20response%20five%20years%20ago.%20Now%20it's%20a%20%2450%20billion%20business.%3Cp%3ELexie%20Moreland%2FWWD%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E%20launched%20Reels%20in%202020%20as%20a%20TikTok%20clone.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20worked%20really%20well%3A%20It's%20now%20on%20track%20to%20do%20%2450%20billion%20a%20year%20in%20ad%20revenue%2C%20says%20Mark%20Zuckerberg.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEven%20better%20for%20Meta%3A%20It%20gets%20all%20of%20its%20content%20for%20free%2C%20or%20close%20to%20it.%20So%20why%20don't%20creators%20push%20for%20something%20better%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERemember%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-creators-earn-money-facebook-ads-stars-subscriptions-reels-bonuses-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EReels%20was%20dismissed%20as%20Meta's%20attempt%20to%20clone%20TikTok%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20now%20the%20five-year-old%20app%20is%20on%20track%20to%20generate%20%2450%20billion%20a%20year.%20It's%20turned%20into%20a%20huge%20win%20for%20Meta%2C%20and%20it%20has%20become%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20%26quot%3Bcreator%20economy%26quot%3B%20businesses%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20number%20also%20makes%20something%20else%20clear%3A%20The%20creator%20economy's%20biggest%20winners%20aren't%20creators.%20It's%20the%20platforms%20that%20depend%20on%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20almost%20every%20one%20of%20those%20platforms%20depends%20on%20the%20labor%20of%20creators%20%E2%80%94%20a%20shorter%20way%20of%20describing%20%26quot%3Bpeople%20who%20make%20and%2For%20own%20content%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20but%20shares%20very%20little%20of%20the%20revenue%20those%20creators'%20stuff%20generates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20one%20major%20exception%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoutube-donald-trump-podcasts-joe-rogan2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle's%20YouTube%2C%20which%20is%20also%20a%20%2450%20billion%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20which%2C%20until%20recently%2C%20shared%20about%20half%20of%20all%20the%20money%20its%20videos%20made%20with%20the%20people%20who%20made%20the%20videos.%20Everyone%20else%20%E2%80%94Meta%2C%20TikTok%2C%20Snap%20%E2%80%94%20offers%20a%20different%20deal%2C%20which%20goes%20like%20this%3A%20%3Cem%3EGive%20us%20your%20stuff%2C%20for%20free.%20Maybe%20we'll%20give%20a%20small%20subset%20of%20you%20some%20kind%20of%20bonus%20from%20a%20%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.tiktok.com%2Fen%2Fbusiness-and-creator%2Fcreator-rewards-program%2Fcreator-rewards-program%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecreator%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20or%20something%20like%20that.%20But%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20we'll%20make%20money%20selling%20ads%20against%20your%20stuff%20on%20our%20platform%20%E2%80%94%20and%20you'll%20have%20to%20find%20another%20way%20to%20make%20money.%20You're%20welcome!%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20news%20to%20people%20in%20and%20around%20the%20creator%20economy%20(again%3A%20you%20could%20just%20say%20%26quot%3Bmedia%20business%26quot%3B).%20But%20Meta's%20boast%20about%20its%20success%20%E2%80%94%20made%20by%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20last%20month%2C%20during%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fs21.q4cdn.com%2F399680738%2Ffiles%2Fdoc_financials%2F2025%2Fq3%2FMETA-Q3-2025-Earnings-Call-Transcript.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EQ3%20earnings%20call%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20puts%20it%20in%20sharp%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20build%20a%20%2450%20billion%20a%20year%20business%20doing%20anything%2C%20anywhere.%20But%20a%20%2450%20billion%20business%20built%20on%20other%20people's%20content%20that%20you%20get%20more%20or%20less%20for%20free%3F%20That's%20pretty%20special.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20better%20for%20Meta%20and%20its%20peers%3A%20There's%20no%20sense%20that%20any%20of%20this%20is%20going%20to%20change.%20Every%20so%20often%2C%20someone%20will%20tell%20me%20about%20their%20plan%20to%20make%20it%20happen%3A%20They'll%20convince%20a%20bunch%20of%20content%20creators%20to%20take%20their%20stuff%20off%20the%20non-sharing%20platforms%20unless%20they%20get%20a%20better%20deal.%20It%20never%20happens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Meta%20and%20its%20peers%20have%20a%20pretty%20good%20argument%20for%20why%20that%20doesn't%20happen%2C%20though%20they%20generally%20don't%20say%20this%20out%20loud%20(I've%20asked%20Meta%20for%20comment).%20It's%20that%20their%20massive%20platforms%20offer%20creators%20the%20promise%20of%20exposure%2C%20which%20they%20can%20parlay%20into%20businesses%20they%20can%20build%20on%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESure%2C%20maybe%20Meta%20isn't%20going%20to%20give%20you%20a%20meaningful%20cut%20of%20the%20money%20it%20makes%20selling%20ads%20against%20your%20videos.%20But%20someone%20%3Cem%3Eelse%3C%2Fem%3E%20may%20pay%20you%20a%20bunch%20of%20money%20to%20feature%20their%20product%20in%20one%20of%20your%20videos.%20Win%2C%20win.%20And%20if%20you%20don't%20like%20it%2C%20go%20find%20another%20huge%20platform%20that%20gives%20you%20a%20better%20deal.%20Good%20luck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20there%20is%20one%20place%20to%20get%20a%20better%20deal%2C%20which%20is%20YouTube.%20The%20world's%20biggest%20video%20site%20kicked%20off%20the%20creator%20economy%20way%20back%20in%202007%2C%20when%20it%20launched%20its%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fcreators%2Fpartner-program%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epartner%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20still%20exists%20today.%20That%20one%20gives%20(most)%20big%20YouTube%20video-makers%2055%25%20of%20any%20ad%20dollars%20attached%20to%20their%20videos.%20And%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fallthingsd.com%2F20130304%2Fyoutubes-show-me-the-money-problem%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYouTube%20creators%20have%20spent%20years%20complaining%20about%20that%20split%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it's%20still%20the%20best%20deal%20in%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20haven't%20other%20platforms%20tried%20to%20do%20the%20same%20thing%3F%20I%20ask%20them%20all%20the%20time.%20Sometimes%20they'll%20mention%20that%20it's%20difficult%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20share%20revenue%20for%20videos%20you%20swipe%20past%20in%20a%20vertical%20feed.%20But%20the%20real%20answer%20is%20that%20they've%20found%20they%20don't%20have%20to%20%E2%80%94%20why%20pay%20for%20something%20you%20can%20get%20for%20free%3F%20The%20margins%20are%20way%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20YouTube%2C%20the%20one%20platform%20that%20built%20real%20economics%20for%20creators%2C%20is%20backing%20away%20a%20bit.%20Shorts%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3Eits%3C%2Fem%3E%20TikTok%20clone%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.google.com%2Fyoutube%2Fanswer%2F12504220%3Fhl%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egives%20creators%20a%20smaller%20cut%2C%20and%20ties%20payouts%20to%20a%20shared%20pool%20of%20ad%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20not%20their%20actual%20videos.%20The%20message%20is%20clear%3A%20Even%20the%20platform%20that%20started%20out%20sharing%20the%20pie%20would%20like%20to%20keep%20more%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20not%3F%20It%20works%20for%20Meta%2C%20and%20everyone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-reels-creator-economy-revenue-advertising-youtube-50-billion-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1763114461000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69165c6be1a9cbb014de30cc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-reels-creator-economy-revenue-advertising-youtube-50-billion-2025-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Reels%20is%20on%20track%20to%20generate%20%2450%20billion%20a%20year.%20Even%20better%20for%20Meta%3A%20It%20gets%20all%20of%20its%20content%20for%20free%2C%20or%20close%20to%20it.%20Why%20do%20creators%20do%20it%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22pkafka%40insider.com%20(Peter%20Kafka)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-reels-creator-economy-revenue-advertising-youtube-50-billion-2025-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meta%20is%20tapping%20top%20talent%20into%20robotics%20efforts%2C%20including%20the%20leader%20behind%20its%20smart%20glasses%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222227%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Li-Chen%20Miller%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69167715e1a9cbb014de3229%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221488%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELi-Chen%20Miller%3Cp%3EJOSH%20EDELSON%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELi-Chen%20Miller%2C%20who%20led%20Meta's%20smart%20glasses%2C%20became%20the%20first%20product%20manager%20of%20its%20robotics%20team.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20robotics%20group%20aims%20to%20develop%20products%20like%20humanoid%20robots%20for%20use%20in%20homes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMeta's%20robotics%20push%20aligns%20with%20its%20AI%20ambitions%20and%20recent%20high-profile%20engineering%20hires.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20is%20ramping%20up%20its%20fledgling%20robotics%20effort%20by%20hiring%20AI%20talent%20and%20moving%20one%20of%20its%20most%20influential%20hardware%20leaders%20to%20that%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELi-Chen%20Miller%2C%20who%20led%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-connect-glasses-ai-superintelligence-group-connect-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMeta's%20smart%20glasses%3C%2Fa%3E%20portfolio%2C%20including%20its%20prototype%20Orion%20augmented%20reality%20glasses%2C%20has%20become%20the%20first%20product%20manager%20of%20Reality%20Labs'%20new%20Robotics%20group%2C%20according%20to%20an%20internal%20post%20seen%20by%20Business%20Insider%20and%20later%20posted%20on%20LinkedIn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWrapping%20up%20our%202025%20launches%2C%20it%20feels%20weird%20to%20leave%20Wearables%2C%26quot%3B%20Miller%20wrote%20in%20her%20post%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20I'm%20truly%20pumped%20to%20go%20be%20the%20first%20PM%20on%20RL's%20Robotics%20team%20-%20bring%20it%20on%2C%20RoboCats%20of%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiller's%20move%20is%20another%20sign%20that%20Meta%20is%20getting%20serious%20about%20robotics.%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20the%20company%20established%20a%20dedicated%20group%20within%20Reality%20Labs%20led%20by%20former%20Cruise%20CEO%20Marc%20Whitten%20to%20develop%20humanoid%20robots%20capable%20of%20assisting%20with%20physical%20household%20tasks%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2025-02-14%2Fmeta-plans-major-investment-into-ai-powered-humanoid-robots%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20this%20week%2C%20Meta%20had%20about%2040%20robotics-related%20job%20openings%20on%20its%20careers%20website.%20Some%20of%20those%20positions%20include%20a%20director%20of%20robotics%20product%20operations%20to%20lead%20a%20team%20to%20deliver%20%26quot%3Bworld-class%20robotics%20products%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20AI%20research%20scientist%20to%20%26quot%3Binvent%20data-driven%20paradigms%20for%20robotics%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20multiple%20software%20engineers%20in%20robotics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiller%20announced%20her%20m