r%20protection%20agency%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20push%20relief%20for%20student-loan%20borrowers%20further%20out%20of%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAttorneys%20for%20Russell%20Vought%2C%20acting%20director%20of%20the%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%2C%20wrote%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.cadc.41898%2Fgov.uscourts.cadc.41898.01208794293.0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20legal%20filing%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20November%2010%20that%20the%20administration%20%26quot%3Banticipates%20exhausting%26quot%3B%20the%20CFPB's%20available%20funds%20in%20early%202026%2C%20meaning%20that%20after%20that%20point%2C%20the%20agency%20created%20in%202011%20to%20protect%20Americans%20from%20another%20financial%20crisis%20will%20be%20defunct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVought%20wrote%20in%20a%20memo%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-debt-relief-borrowers-cfpb-scotus-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20CFPB's%20funding%20structure%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20relies%20on%20money%20from%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%2C%20is%20not%20constitutional%2C%20marking%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20most%20significant%20step%20to%20date%20in%20attempting%20to%20shut%20down%20the%20agency.%20Vought%20argued%20that%20the%20agency%20can%20only%20draw%20from%20the%20Fed%20when%20the%20central%20bank%20is%20turning%20a%20profit%2C%20which%20it%20has%20not%20done%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20rid%20of%20the%20CFPB%20would%20remove%20a%20level%20of%20oversight%20on%20financial%20institutions%20%E2%80%94%20and%20also%20raises%20increased%20risks%20for%20student-loan%20borrowers%2C%20John%20Rao%2C%20a%20senior%20attorney%20with%20the%20National%20Consumer%20Law%20Center%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEarlier%20administrations%20have%20worked%20closely%20with%20the%20CFPB%20to%20ensure%20that%20servicers%20comply%20with%20the%20contracts%20they%20