s%20and%20eroded%20trust%20in%20the%20Marriott%20brand.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20meltdown%20was%20a%20lesson%20in%20how%20not%20to%20handle%20a%20crisis%2C%20PR%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20companies%20did%20not%20take%20accountability%20and%20lost%20control%20of%20the%20narrative%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarriott-sonder-agreement-terminated-meltdown-unraveled-chaos-customers-help-bonvoy-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMarriott-Sonder%20fallout%3C%2Fa%3E%20served%20as%20a%20lesson%20in%20what%20not%20to%20do%20during%20a%20corporate%20crisis%2C%20public%20relations%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20week%2C%20chaos%20ensued%20at%20short-term%20rental%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsonder-marriott-bankruptcy-cofounder-ceo-francis-davidson-shocked-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESonder's%20properties%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20Marriott%20ended%20their%20licensing%20agreement%20on%20Sunday.%20A%20day%20later%2C%20Sonder%20announced%20that%20it%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsonder-holdings-bankruptcy-chapter-7-liquidation-marriott-bookings-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efile%20for%20Chapter%207%20bankruptcy.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarriott-sonder-derailed-dream-vacation-single-mother-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGuests%20staying%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Sonder%20properties%20were%20given%20notice%20at%20the%20eleventh%20hour%20to%20vacate%20their%20rooms%2C%20forcing%20them%20to%20book%20alternative%20accommodations%20at%20sometimes%3Cstrong%3E-%3C%2Fstrong%3Eexorbitant%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20pair%20of%20crisis%20communications%20experts%20say%20Marriott's%20biggest%20mistake%20was%20losing%20control%20of%20the%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20Marriott%20and%20Sonder%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20several%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22313cef55-affa-47cd-ae38-136712c9a7d1%5C%22%3ELosing%20control%20of%20the%20narrative%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEvan%20Nierman%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Florida-based%20crisis%20public%20relations%20firm%20Red%20Banyan%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Marriott%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Elost%20control%20of%20the%20crisis%20messaging%20the%20moment%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarriott-sonder-hotel-chain-bankruptcy-guest-rebook-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epeople%20started%20telling%20their%20stories%3C%2Fa%3E%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Sunday%2C%20guests%20staying%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarriott-sonder-rental-companies-snap-up-clients-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESonder%20properties%3C%2Fa%3E%20began%20posting%20on%20platforms%20like%20X%20and%20TikTok%20about%20being%20forced%20to%20vacate%20their%20rooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20people%20start%20describing%20themselves%20as%20temporarily%20homeless%20because%20of%20your%20brand%2C%20the%20reputational%20damage%20becomes%20hard%20to%20contain%2C%26quot%3B%20Nierman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOliver%20Ellerton%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Singapore-based%20public%20relations%20firm%20Ellerton%20%26amp%3B%20Co.%2C%20said%20Marriott%20failed%20to%20get%20its%20messaging%20out%20quickly.%20Ellerton%20previously%20worked%20as%20the%20PR%20lead%20for%20the%20Ritz-Carlton%20and%20the%20JW%20Marriott%20in%20Kuala%20Lumpur.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGuests%20were%20being%20moved%20out%20while%20call%20centers%20were%20still%20giving%20outdated%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BMarriott%20didn't%20lose%20trust%20because%20they%20made%20a%20difficult%20call%2C%20they%20lost%20trust%20because%20their%20messages%20changed%20faster%20than%20guests%20could%20pack%20their%20suitcases.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20instead%20of%20sending%20emails%2C%20each%20guest%20should%20have%20been%20called%20personally.%20Marriott%20and%20Sonder%20should%20have%20used%20social%20media%20and%20other%20channels%20to%20explain%20the%20situation%20and%20provide%20clear%20next%20steps%2C%20he%20added.%20Sonder's%20last%20Instagram%20post%20was%2017%20weeks%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20importantly%2C%20all%20Marriott%20and%20Sonder%20staff%20should%20be%20aware%20and%20on%20the%20same%20page%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Sonder%20employees%20that%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20said%20they%20were%20as%20blindsided%20by%20the%20Marriott-Sonder%20breakup%20as%20guests%20were.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228210cadc-6a50-4710-8dae-0fa1869393a4%5C%22%3EA%20lack%20of%20accountability%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20mistake%20Marriott%20made%20was%20reversing%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarriott-sonder-ask-credit-card-companies-refund-guests-chargeback-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eposition%20on%20credit%20card%20refunds%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20PR%20gurus%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Sunday%2C%20Marriott%20told%20customers%20that%20those%20who%20had%20booked%20Sonder%20properties%20via%20its%20channels%20would%20get%20full%20refunds.%20But%20a%20few%20days%20later%2C%20the%20company%20changed%20the%20wording%20on%20its%20website%2C%20telling%20customers%20to%20contact%20their%20credit%20card%20companies%20for%20refunds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEllerton%20said%20Marriott's%20first%20instinct%20to%20offer%20refunds%20signaled%20accountability%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20the%20execution%20broke%20down%20almost%20immediately.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENierman%20said%20the%20change%20in%20credit%20card%20guidance%20sent%20mixed%20signals%20and%20made%20it%20seem%20like%20Marriott%20was%20%26quot%3Bsidestepping%20accountability.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20lesson%20is%20that%20hospitality%20companies%20earn%20goodwill%20when%20they%20take%20the%20burden%20off%20the%20customer%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BRelocation%2C%20refunds%2C%20and%20clear%20guidance%20are%20essentials%2C%20not%20perks%2C%20during%20a%20crisis.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223f06dbfc-67bb-4db4-a95c-95c76d687d1a%5C%22%3ESonder's%20bankruptcy%20announcement%20was%20a%20good%20idea%20with%20bad%20execution%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20experts%20agreed%20that%20Sonder's%20announcement%20that%20it%20would%20file%20for%20Chapter%207%20bankruptcy%20was%20a%20good%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSonder%20was%20transparent%20about%20its%20financial%20collapse%2C%20which%20is%20more%20than%20many%20startups%20offer%20when%20the%20walls%20come%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20Nierman%20said.%20%26quot%3BAcknowledging%20the%20severity%20of%20the%20situation%20is%20better%20than%20pretending%20the%20business%20is%20still%20standing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEllerton%20added%20that%20formalizing%20the%20bankruptcy%20filing%20created%20clarity%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bclarity%20delivered%20late%20is%20almost%20indistinguishable%20from%20chaos.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20staff%20and%20guests%20learn%20the%20news%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20that's%20not%20crisis%20communication%2C%20that's%20crisis%20surrender%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2210d31658-ebdb-4499-8ce2-5a60782befca%5C%22%3EPreparation%20and%20planning%20make%20for%20good%20crisis%20comms%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20crisis%20like%20this%20called%20for%20preparation%20and%20a%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEllerton%20said%20Marriott%20should%20have%20set%20up%20a%2024-hour%2C%20specialized%20call%20center%20for%20Sonder%20guests%20exclusively%2C%20processed%20immediate%20refunds%2C%20and%20covered%20the%20cost%20of%20transport%20to%20other%20Marriott%20properties.%20Additional%20perks%2C%20such%20as%20upgrades%2C%20gifts%20upon%20arrival%2C%20and%20spa%20bookings%2C%20would%20have%20been%2